# Curriculum topic dropdown (enforced)

When a user selects **form/grade + subject** for any formulation flow (quizzes, topic tests, flashcards, mock exams, ECZ practice/scenarios, Story Weaver, lesson plans, chat curriculum tools, assessments), **topic MUST be chosen from the syllabus dropdown** — never free-typed when curriculum topics exist.

## Shared contract

- UI: `CurriculumTopicSelect` (`components/curriculum/CurriculumTopicSelect.js`)
- Hook: `useCurriculumTopics` → `GET /api/curriculum-topics?subject=&grade=`
- Server: `assertCurriculumTopicAllowed(subject, grade, topic, { required: true })` from `lib/ai/curriculum-context.js`

## Rules

1. Disable topic until both subject and form/grade are set; clear topic when either changes.
2. Default `allowFreeFormWhenEmpty={false}` — no free-text fallback on formulation screens.
3. Every generation/save API that accepts `topic` must call `assertCurriculumTopicAllowed` (quiz-maker, project-maker, story-weaver, lesson-planner, lesson-plans, flashcards, mock-exam, ecz-practice, ecz-exam-questions, …).
4. Schemes / records of work pull weekly topics from curriculum for the selected subject+grade — do not invent free-form weekly topics in the generator.
5. Do not reintroduce `<Input>` / free-text for topic on formulation pages.

## Adding a new formulation surface

1. Render `<CurriculumTopicSelect subject={…} gradeOrForm={…} value={topic} onChange={…} required allowFreeFormWhenEmpty={false} />`
2. In the API route, `await assertCurriculumTopicAllowed(subject, grade, topic, { required: true })` before generation.
